    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Why not make that an event? And like DOM events, provide a function that would let stop the behavior?\n\nSomething like:\n\n``` js\non('before search', function(helper, preventDefault) {\n  // modify helper\n  // or call preventDefault()\n});\n```\n\n?\n\nI am not used to use helper to cancel actions that would normally happen but yes since the instance is already an event emitter, maybe. Depends on what does it brings more\n",
