    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I think it's better because it allows you to add different hooks from different places\n\nWell having configuration for hooks in multiple places might lead to poorly understandable behavior. For example if you have two hooks set in different places you won't necessarily know exactly what the other one is doing. If both try to do the same thing (like a debounce) it can be pretty messy.\n\n:+1: on your proposition @vvo to have two API's\n",
